reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 12, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great addition to my closet!
reviews.reviewText: I replaced my open wire cubby in my closet and I love. Closet looks so much better. Came packaged really well and easy to build. Really good quality and lots more neat and tidy storage.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 5, 2024
reviews.reviewText: assembly was so easy, 30 minutes tops. I was expecting it to look ugly but I think it looks fine especially with the light wood panel on top. I got the 5 drawer one and the larger drawers can told a large backpack and tote. I put maybe 10 shirts in the smaller drawer and have room for more. Light weight (20lbs?) so it’s easy to move around. Only complaint is that the drawers don’t exactly fit into the space perfectly- there are some gaps.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 8, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Nice, for simple purposes
reviews.reviewText: This little unit is exactly what I needed. I am staying at my daughter's home for a month, where I have my own room, but it has no storage space/furniture. I hate living out of a suitcase, so I ordered this item. It was very easy to assemble, (it took about 10 minutes), and it is exactly what I expected it to be. Now I can get a little more organized while I'm here, and my daughter can use it for future guests.ONE STAR DEDUCTED simply because of the price. While it is a useful product, the only reason I paid $65 plus tax (more than I think it is worth) is because I was somewhat desperate. After all, it's really only a few hollow metal tubes, a piece of particle board, and some cardboard wrapped in cheap fabric.I would say this item's main advantage is that it's a quick, simple fix for a space that needs storage. Having two different sizes of "drawers" is convenient. It would be good for anyone who needs something that:* looks nicer than a bunch of cardboard boxes or plastic totes* needs it quickly and temporarilyThe downside: I don't think this would last long in a room with heavy use, such as a child's room or kitchen. If it were less expensive, I wouldn't mind this aspect so much.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Extremely easy to assemble, assembly tool included.
reviews.reviewText: This little chest of drawers comes in many colors, and in spite of it small stature holds a surprisingly good amount of items. I purchased this to replace an extremely squeaky nightstand. I have a tiny tiny tiny bathroom and needed some thing within arms reach of the bathroom door, which I had reversed, because the bathroom is so small. I had previously purchased similar sets of drawers, so I was familiar with the workings and it does not disappoint on storage and quiet access. I was delighted to find the color that I wanted, and it looks clean and nice in the space.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Overall good but came with dent in the track
reviews.reviewText: Overall I like the look and finish of this. It fits nicely with the aesthetic I’m going for in my closet. I also appreciated how simple the assembly was ~ you just need to screw in some nails and all the nails were the same size so it wasn’t too confusing. I also thought it was a good deal for the price point. The ONLY sad part is that one of the tracks came dented which makes it hard for me to slide in one of the fabric drawers :( I would’ve returned it as soon as I found the dent but by that time, I already assembled it and figured it’s too much of a hassle. Just make sure to thoroughly inspect the product before assembling.
